= The PROIEL web application

== Installation

You need Rails 2.1.1 installed as a RubyGem for this application to work.

Most Ruby dependencies should be handled automatically. Use
    rake gems
to get a list of dependencies and their installation status.

You will also need a installations of the following tools with binaries
in a path accessible to the application:
* graphviz
* SFST

Before starting the application for the first time, run
    make -C lib
to build support files.

To build all of the documentation, the `railroad` gem is also required.

=== Rebuilding the data sources

In order to rebuild the data sources, you will, in addition to the above, need
* mdbtools
* sqlite3
and the following gems
* ruby-xslt
